## Core Web Vitals Targets

### Performance Standards
- **Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)**: < 2.5 seconds
- **Interaction to Next Paint (INP)**: < 200 milliseconds
- **Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)**: < 0.1

### Implementation Requirements
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Implement lazy loading for below-fold content
- Optimize font loading with `font-display: swap`
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Use server-side rendering for critical content

## Content Optimization

### Keyword Strategy
**Primary Keywords:**
- Process automation
- Shopify development
- Custom automation solutions
- E-commerce development
- Web application development

**Secondary Keywords:**
- Make.ai automation
- n8n workflows
- Shopify apps
- Custom web solutions
- Business process automation

### Content Structure
- Use H1 for main page title (only one per page)
- Structure content with H2-H6 hierarchy
- Include target keywords naturally in headings
- Write descriptive alt text for all images
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Technical SEO Requirements

### URL Structure
- Use kebab-case: `/services/shopify-development`
- Include target keywords in URLs
- Keep URLs under 60 characters
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)

### Internal Linking
- Link to related services and pages
- Use descriptive anchor text
- Create topic clusters around main services
- Include breadcrumb navigation

### Site Architecture
- Create XML sitemap automatically
- Implement robots.txt
- Use proper redirects (301 for permanent)
- Set up canonical URLs

## Audit Questions
Before publishing any page, verify:
- Is the page title unique and under 60 characters?
- Does the meta description compelling and under 160 characters?
- Are all images optimized with proper alt text?
- Is the content structured with proper headings?
- Are Core Web Vitals targets met?
- Is schema markup implemented correctly?
- Are internal links relevant and helpful?
- Does the page load in under 3 seconds?

## Error Handling
- Implement proper 404 pages
- Set up error monitoring
- Create custom error pages that maintain SEO value
- Monitor for broken links and redirects

